The '''28th Marine Regiment''' (28th Marines) is an inactive [[infantry]] regiment of the [[United States Marine Corps]].  They fought during the [[Battle of Iwo Jima]] in [[World War II]] and some of its members were immortalized in the famous photo of the [[Raising the Flag on Iwo Jima|flag raising]] on top of [[Mount Suribachi]]. 

== Subordinate Units ==

The Regiment was comprised of three [[infantry]] [[battalion]]s and one headquarters battalion:
